Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.23,0:01:45.15,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember the first time we met, Kimblee?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.15,0:01:47.05,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,It seems our positions are now reversed!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.38,0:01:49.21,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you dare look down on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.21,0:01:55.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Kimblee, you bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.88,0:01:59.87,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why... Why is Winry here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.87,0:02:03.47,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We were just about to capture Scar, but now he's taken her hostage!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.47,0:02:05.10,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Move.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.85,0:02:09.94,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.52,0:02:14.32,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Stop, Crimson Alchemist!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.77,0:02:17.40,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Do you not see Winry in front of you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.88,0:02:23.03,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get in my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.35,0:02:35.07,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it, Scar!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.07,0:02:38.30,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Kimblee, don't go near the building! It's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.84,0:02:41.51,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Withdraw!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.16,0:02:44.26,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,There's a blizzard approaching! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.34,0:02:53.09,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,You're a fantastic actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.41,0:02:55.02,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That wasn't an act.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.84,0:03:02.53,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm actually furious at myself for being such a coward and having to put up such an act.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.13,0:03:08.66,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you kill my parents? {ep38}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.23,0:03:12.92,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what I say, it'll be only an excuse. {ep38}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.62,0:03:17.71,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,The fact is I killed the Rockbells. {ep38}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.10,0:03:19.17,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,With this hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.31,0:03:30.68,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Girl, you have the right to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.74,0:03:45.78,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, you'll die from blood loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.78,0:03:47.02,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Winry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.02,0:03:47.94,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.31,0:03:52.46,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure Mom and Dad would have done the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.60,0:03:58.20,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,It's a life Mom and Dad saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.91,0:04:00.88,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure there's a meaning to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.99,0:04:04.18,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying you'll forgive me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.18,0:04:08.18,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get the wrong idea! I haven't forgiven you for killing my parents unjustly!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.11,0:04:20.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Winry...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.19,0:04:24.54,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry; I'm not going to cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.48,0:04:30.87,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I promise you that the next time I cry, it'd be with tears of joy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.88,0:04:41.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Scar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.96,0:04:50.97,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Despite what Winry just said, I still want to beat you to a pulp and drag you over to the Rockbells' graves.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.05,0:04:57.80,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Should I contact Headquarters?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.80,0:04:58.50,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.84,0:05:00.98,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I believe Miles was your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.27,0:05:03.82,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Can I ask something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.22,0:05:05.24,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.38,0:05:08.74,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,You called me a fellow countryman, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.36,0:05:10.23,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.53,0:05:12.95,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Until my grandfather's generation, my ancestors were full Ishbalans.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.09,0:05:19.33,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I wish we could have met under different circumstances, my red-eyed brethren.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.19,0:05:24.13,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you siding with the Amestrian army?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.31,0:05:32.81,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Because I wish to change the way people feel about Ishbalans from within the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.15,0:05:39.56,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt people would change the way they feel so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.18,0:05:43.32,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how long it'll take.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.02,0:05:47.84,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,But there are things only I,\Na man of mixed parentage, can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.76,0:05:52.87,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I'm nothing but an Ishbalan pebble that was thrown into the Amestrian army.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.36,0:05:57.92,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,But there may come a time when\Na small ripple becomes a giant wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.29,0:06:07.34,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,And ironically, the person who made me realize that is a full-blooded Amestrian.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.43,0:06:16.26,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I'm nothing but a mass of hatred, born from that civil war.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.49,0:06:21.23,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad someone like you exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.61,0:06:24.43,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Major.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.70,0:06:28.67,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Is this Headquarters?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.67,0:06:30.11,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,This is Miles speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.78,0:06:33.03,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,We've captured Scar in a building in Area D.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.51,0:06:35.37,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Let Kimblee know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.27,0:06:43.27,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what your circumstances are,\NI can't just let you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.85,0:06:45.88,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,You deserve to be tried and sentenced.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.88,0:06:47.04,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.57,0:06:48.26,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.56,0:06:50.42,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,May!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.50,0:06:52.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor Marcoh!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.32,0:06:56.28,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't take that man away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.25,0:07:03.27,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad, Sir Kimblee.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.67,0:07:07.03,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,The clouds are moving fast.\NThe weather's about to get pretty ugly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.60,0:07:10.86,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.24,0:07:13.78,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Deciphering research documents?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.36,0:07:20.29,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,It's breakthrough research that combines the alchemies from Amestris and Xing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.72,0:07:24.94,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,But the essential portions are written in ancient Ishbalan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.64,0:07:28.27,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,The only one who can read this is Scar.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.27,0:07:29.22,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.31,0:07:34.19,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,You're the girl who knows Eastern Alchemy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.78,0:07:37.79,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I've received orders to take you back to the fort.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.79,0:07:39.79,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! M-Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.21,0:07:41.36,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.73,0:07:43.68,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I've been ordered to give you a warm reception.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.06,0:07:47.38,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Now... if Scar can't be caught...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.86,0:07:51.57,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,...and if we also can't let them know that Marcoh is here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.02,0:07:57.74,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,It might be better to just hide them at Briggs for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.74,0:08:00.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on, what the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.64,0:08:02.71,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You're taking {\i1}him{\i0}, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.41,0:08:06.08,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you guys need him to decipher the documents?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.79,0:08:09.17,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It pisses me off to think we have to ask {\i1}him{\i0\fscx30} {\r} for help...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.17,0:08:11.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we just hand him over to Kimblee and-
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.16,0:08:12.59,Default-alt,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,A transmutation circle made from this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.92,0:08:16.26,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,And the history of this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.76,0:08:19.11,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard everything from General Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.81,0:08:23.70,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Something is about to happen;\Nsomething that will encompass all of Amestris.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.46,0:08:28.78,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't deciphering the documents of higher priority than anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.86,0:08:34.55,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also aware that Ms. Rockbell has been taken hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.22,0:08:39.58,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,If we do this now, we could make Kimblee take the blame and hide her away at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.16,0:08:50.92,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Scar, if you decide to lend us a hand,\Nwe can postpone your trial to a later date.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.45,0:08:52.22,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.55,0:08:56.34,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I have no other options, do I?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.17,0:08:58.97,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I promise to cooperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.31,0:09:01.85,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really mean it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.60,0:09:07.35,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I swear on my Ishbalan blood, my red-eyed brethren.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.47,0:09:09.79,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,So, that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.32,0:09:14.61,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but you're going to have to wait a little longer for him to face trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.70,0:09:16.28,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.76,0:09:21.56,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, I forgot about these two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.86,0:09:22.62,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.62,0:09:23.32,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.32,0:09:24.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.54,0:09:27.61,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on! You don't have to kill them!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.61,0:09:29.73,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing to be gained from letting them live.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.73,0:09:30.25,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.25,0:09:34.87,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't about gain or loss! Isn't there something you could do besides killing them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.95,0:09:38.54,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,Showing us pity, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.54,0:09:42.09,Default,Zan,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need for that. You're just a kid who doesn't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.60,0:09:45.77,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,There's no future for us anyway, since we've got bodies like these.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.77,0:09:47.55,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to kill us, just do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.19,0:09:52.90,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you two have family or people important to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.90,0:09:54.18,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,Of course we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.62,0:09:58.33,Default,Zan,0000,0000,0000,,But when we were transformed to this state, we were publicly pronounced dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.87,0:10:00.03,Default,Zan,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't seen them since.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.56,0:10:02.43,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you {\i1}want{\i0\fscx30} {\r} to see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.43,0:10:05.79,Default,Zan,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we did, there's nothing we could do. Look at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.65,0:10:11.51,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so you don't want to return to your old selves?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.51,0:10:14.20,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,You're fine with those bodies, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.20,0:10:15.47,Default,Zan,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.47,0:10:17.55,Default,Jan,0000,0000,0000,,Of course we want to return to normal!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.59,0:10:20.11,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Then there's your answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.26,0:10:24.97,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't talk as though you've already given up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.97,0:10:28.95,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't even explored the possibility of returning to your old bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.66,0:10:33.10,Default,Jan,0000,0000,0000,,How the hell would {\i1}you{\i0\fscx30} {\r} know how we feel?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.10,0:10:35.15,Default,Zan,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way to-
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.89,0:10:42.31,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to get my body back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.72,0:10:46.35,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many years it may take, I'll never give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.30,0:10:49.26,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Major!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.81,0:10:51.66,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.66,0:10:52.38,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.90,0:10:54.14,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,A blizzard is approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.79,0:10:57.88,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible to march in a blizzard with the equipment we have right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.48,0:11:00.87,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, we won't make it back to the fort.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.95,0:11:03.14,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.52,0:11:05.78,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this a mining town?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.78,0:11:08.14,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we just take the underground mining path?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.81,0:11:11.34,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.77,0:11:17.85,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's just that since this is such a big mine, I figured there might be a path leading through the mountain...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.02,0:11:20.70,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,I-I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.15,0:11:21.25,Default-alt,Both,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.70,0:11:22.28,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Yoki!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.28,0:11:24.99,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,I used to own a coal mine, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.78,0:11:28.75,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,That would work! The mine exits beyond the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.75,0:11:29.79,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.33,0:11:33.67,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,If you happen to encounter a soldier from Briggs, hand them this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.69,0:11:38.46,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I've stated the situation in there, so they should give you refuge.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.46,0:11:39.71,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in your debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.92,0:11:43.68,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,I guess the only thing we still have to account for is the girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.58,0:11:53.23,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Even if she comes with us, wouldn't the Elric Brothers be the prime suspects if they find out she's missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.15,0:11:55.48,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We'll figure something out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.48,0:11:59.21,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mean to brag, but we can work as well as we can talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.21,0:12:02.93,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,No, Kimblee is a very suspicious man.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.32,0:12:06.12,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't plan this completely, he'll be doubly suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.54,0:12:17.18,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... this may be a bit strange coming from me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.84,0:12:19.09,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.52,0:12:23.97,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What if I were kidnapped by Scar?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.84,0:12:32.56,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,"Kidnapped"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.03,0:12:34.84,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So... what you mean is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.27,0:12:37.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We free him, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.93,0:12:46.12,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Scar runs off with me in his arms, and you pretend like you're desperately trying to stop him...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.80,0:12:47.57,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,...or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.57,0:12:50.04,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think we'll let you do something that dangerous?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.24,0:12:51.20,Default-alt,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a hostage right now, anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.59,0:12:55.04,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I have to risk my life to escape, or it'll never happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.04,0:12:57.19,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,But with Scar?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.19,0:13:00.67,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! You don't need to risk {\i1}your{\i0\fscx30} {\r} life!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.84,0:13:05.34,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Quit trying to do everything by yourselves! I'm tired of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.34,0:13:11.96,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and decide. The blizzard is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.51,0:13:15.12,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty soon, we won't even be able to leave this building.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.38,0:13:21.90,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Kimblee's squad is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.25,0:13:27.04,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.43,0:13:30.48,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Scar, if anything happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.48,0:13:33.37,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I know. I plan to keep my promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.09,0:13:39.08,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,Could you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.83,0:13:42.59,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,Could you take us, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.97,0:13:46.34,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,I understand you don't trust us,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.34,0:13:49.46,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,so you can keep us bound.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.16,0:13:53.52,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Kimblee shows no mercy to men who can't do their job.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.52,0:13:55.43,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,We'll get killed either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.43,0:13:56.35,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,And besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.93,0:13:58.94,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,...we don't want to give up, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.71,0:14:03.23,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,We can trust you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.69,0:14:10.32,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,If you two happen to betray us and get in our way, this country could fall to ruin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.70,0:14:13.49,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Including the people you two hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.37,0:14:16.50,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on! What do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.03,0:14:20.16,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,Central never told us anything like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.16,0:14:23.04,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us the details! What is this about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.14,0:14:32.33,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Is this fine?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.09,0:14:36.45,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. You all will probably feel safer this way, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.62,0:14:40.23,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Scar, we're going to have to ask you to put on an act.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.83,0:14:42.23,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.23,0:14:46.48,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Keep the vow you swore on your Ishbalan blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.62,0:14:54.91,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You need to take off your earrings!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.35,0:14:58.03,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Those are made out of metal, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.41,0:15:00.54,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't take them off, you'll get frostbite.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.05,0:15:09.83,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Ed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.93,0:15:13.55,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on to these for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.00,0:15:17.47,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be waiting for you at the fort!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.53,0:15:30.49,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Kimblee, you bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.49,0:15:33.59,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why the hell didn't you keep an eye on Winry?! {ep38}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.73,0:15:51.50,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worried about Zampano and Jerso.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.93,0:15:55.76,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,They were either killed by Scar, or they can't move because of the blizzard...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.76,0:15:58.28,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Scar shouldn't be able to move, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.28,0:16:00.86,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,He has to be in this town somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.86,0:16:04.02,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,We ought to plan our next search while we're sitting here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.17,0:16:08.58,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,This blizzard really saved us...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.33,0:16:11.95,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I pray that all of you will make it to the fort.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.06,0:16:16.12,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Major Miles, you have a phone call from Briggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.87,0:16:20.76,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Miles speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.73,0:16:24.58,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.34,0:16:33.34,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so you're the daughter of those Rockbells.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.93,0:16:36.09,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You've heard of my parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.09,0:16:41.60,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't a single doctor who was in Ishbal who hasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.08,0:16:45.60,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,They fulfilled their duties as doctors without any regard for their own lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.94,0:16:50.53,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't forgiven that you killed my parents unjustly!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.40,0:16:54.87,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,You must endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.87,0:16:58.18,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,So you're telling me to forgive the army for what they did?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.18,0:17:00.54,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,"Enduring" and "forgiving" are two different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.54,0:17:03.16,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,You must not forgive the unjustness of society.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.16,0:17:05.75,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,As a human being, you must hold the event in contempt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.75,0:17:08.67,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, you must endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.67,0:17:11.96,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,You must put an end to the chain of hatred!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.26,0:17:16.87,Default,Bro,0000,0000,0000,,If many negative emotions gather,\Nthey will end up influencing the entire world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.42,0:17:22.47,Default,Bro,0000,0000,0000,,But on the other hand, it is also possible to gather positive emotions and lead the world in that direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.72,0:17:27.55,Default,Bro,0000,0000,0000,,That is why I study alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.42,0:17:33.32,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, here we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.97,0:17:35.57,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,What is this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.22,0:17:38.45,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,It's a post for mine officers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.45,0:17:39.60,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,There should be...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.60,0:17:41.16,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.16,0:17:44.23,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,See? A detailed map of the mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.71,0:17:46.25,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,It looks pretty complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.25,0:17:48.24,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand what goes where.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.24,0:17:51.09,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,We can just take this path here, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.09,0:17:53.57,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, you're pretty amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.57,0:17:55.97,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Keep the compliments coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.55,0:18:00.94,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,With this, we should be able to reach the other side of the mountain a lot faster than we thought we would.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.98,0:18:08.44,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Doctor Marcoh... Do you think those research documents hold anything to get us back to our old bodies?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.90,0:18:10.35,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,There is a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.79,0:18:14.19,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,It's tough to say because it's not a form of alchemy we're familiar with.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.19,0:18:16.37,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,I've got faith, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.37,0:18:19.42,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,I really want to see my family!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.32,0:18:23.03,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Even though your wife was always leading you by the nose?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.03,0:18:25.83,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,You probably only want to see your daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.83,0:18:31.39,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,Look who's talking! You always turn nasty when you're drunk, so your son was just about fed up with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.39,0:18:33.67,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,You still have the guts to see him now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.67,0:18:35.49,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,That was brutal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.14,0:18:40.24,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong, May?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.63,0:18:41.50,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.80,0:18:47.98,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,I was just wondering when I'll be able to return, since my people are waiting for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.98,0:18:54.74,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,The philosopher's stone uses the lives of humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.06,0:18:57.99,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,I mustn't seek such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.53,0:19:01.32,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I tell him how to create one,\Nwithout bringing back an actual stone,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.32,0:19:04.72,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,the Emperor would make plans to create one without hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.33,0:19:08.38,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,By sacrificing the lives of many people...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.16,0:19:13.58,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Immortality... Just what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.58,0:19:18.84,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,That answer may also be hidden in those research documents.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.45,0:19:22.70,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,So let's try to get to the fort as quickly as we can to decipher them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.33,0:19:24.44,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.44,0:19:27.23,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The fort is no longer safe?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.23,0:19:30.85,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Major General Armstrong has been summoned to Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.44,0:19:34.29,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Many soldiers from Central are now stationed at the fort, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.91,0:19:37.87,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Kimblee must have proposed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.87,0:19:42.03,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,He was making quite a few phone calls while at the fort, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.71,0:19:45.62,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on. If the Major General is no longer there...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.07,0:19:49.87,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,An officer loyal to Bradley is going to be stationed there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.87,0:19:51.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So, Winry and the rest of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.66,0:19:54.22,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to be a lot more difficult to hide them there now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.52,0:19:57.67,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,That's hardly the issue. If things take a turn for the worse, they could fall in the hands of the enemy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.91,0:20:04.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We have to let them know somehow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.43,0:20:07.93,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,It would be impossible to go after them in this blizzard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.93,0:20:10.04,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't just leave them!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.04,0:20:11.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.33,0:20:14.04,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,An amateur shouldn't take a blizzard lightly!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.04,0:20:17.27,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It'll suck out all your strength in a matter of minutes, leaving you to freeze to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.36,0:20:20.05,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,There's another option.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.25,0:20:27.22,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,There's someone here with a body that knows no fatigue and won't freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.09,0:20:37.18,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,This is worse than I expected...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.59,0:20:41.01,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Now, where's the landmark...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.91,0:20:42.82,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.90,0:20:51.81,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see anything with the snow blowing everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.81,0:21:21.30,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,What was that just now? My body?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.05,0:21:24.93,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.63,0:21:30.47,Default,66,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible to place a soul on a body that doesn't belong. {ep19}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.67,0:21:35.13,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,A body that shouldn't possess a soul...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.52,0:21:36.72,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,A rejection reaction!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.02,0:21:41.94,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,My old body is pulling my soul towards it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.95,0:21:49.03,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! Get it together!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.62,0:21:53.45,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I have to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.37,0:22:00.83,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,Alphonse Elric.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.34,0:22:05.92,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,Edward Elric.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.31,0:22:09.47,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.97,0:22:13.69,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,...Van Hohenheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.35,0:22:19.23,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,Izumi Curtis is also a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.52,0:22:25.31,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,Just one more.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.76,0:24:00.12,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,A departure toward an unknown world.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.12,0:24:03.57,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,It's due to one's heart seeking something new.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.07,0:24:07.37,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,A human can never go against the wishes of his heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.37,0:24:11.17,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,but conflict always arises in that moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.99,0:24:16.39,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.39,0:24:19.29,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 40, Homunculus.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.89,0:24:22.36,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The righteous isn't the one to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.36,0:24:25.61,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The one to overcome the boundaries shall stand as the winner.
